{{see|Ancien Régime}}

==French==
===Etymology===
French ''Ancient Régime'', ''Old Rule'', ''Old Order''; the word first appeared in English in print in 1794.

===Noun===
'''Ancien Régime''' (''plural:'' (only used for the second definition) '''[[anciens régimes]]''')

# {{cattag|pejorative connotation}} A system of government long since supplanted by another, particularly a state of [[feudalism]] with an absolute monarchy supported by divine right.

